                <h3 class="my-3">Architectural and Cultural Significance</h3>                
                <p>Rabindra Bhawan is a testament to the blend of colonial and Indian architectural styles. The structure is built primarily of soil, without the use of rocks, and is surrounded by lush greenery, adding to its charm. The building is not only an administrative block of Tilka Manjhi Bhagalpur University but also houses the office of the Archaeological Department of the university.</p>                
                <h3 class="my-3">Current Usage and Maintenance</h3>
                <p>Rabindra Bhawan serves as the administrative headquarters of Tilka Manjhi Bhagalpur University. Despite its historical significance and scenic location, the building suffers from inadequate maintenance. Efforts to beautify and maintain the site have, at times, resulted in the loss of some of its historical elements and identity.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Tourism and Visitor Experience</h3>
                <p>Rabindra Bhawan is a popular destination for tourists and locals alike. Its historical significance, combined with its picturesque setting, makes it a must-visit spot in Bhagalpur. The site is particularly popular among morning walkers who enjoy the serene environment and the panoramic views of the city and the Ganges River.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">Accessibility</h3>
                <p>Rabindra Bhawan is located approximately 4.7 kilometers from Bhagalpur in Sitanabad. The site is easily accessible from various parts of the city, making it a convenient destination for visitors interested in exploring Bhagalpur's rich historical heritage.</p>
